diff --git a/long_term_tsf/scripts/vision_verification/README.md b/long_term_tsf/scripts/vision_verification/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..158801c
--- /dev/null
+++ b/long_term_tsf/scripts/vision_verification/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,115 @@
+# VisionTS Verification Scripts
+
+This directory runs a zero-shot verification matrix for checking whether VisionTS gains come from the visual MAE pathway or from the numerical time-series structure used to render the image.
+
+## What Is Compared
+
+Each dataset and prediction length runs:
+
+- `SeasonalNaive`: repeats the last observed period with the same `periodicity` used by VisionTS.
+- `VisionTS/none`: the official VisionTS path.
+- `VisionTS/stats_only`: zeros the normalized input after mean/std are computed.
+- `VisionTS/time_reverse`: reverses the normalized lookback sequence.
+- `VisionTS/time_permute`: deterministically permutes the normalized lookback sequence.
+- `VisionTS/row_shuffle`: shuffles rows in the rendered periodic image.
+- `VisionTS/col_shuffle`: shuffles columns in the rendered periodic image.
+- `VisionTS/image_patch_shuffle`: shuffles MAE-size patches in the visible image area.
+
+All runs use `train_epochs=0` and the official long-term forecasting metric pipeline.
+
+## Expected Layout
+
+Run scripts from this repository after placing data and checkpoints in the usual official locations:
+
+```text
+VisionTS/
+  ckpt/
+    mae_visualize_vit_base.pth
+  long_term_tsf/
+    dataset/
+      ETT-small/
+        ETTm1.csv
+        ETTm2.csv
+        ETTh1.csv
+        ETTh2.csv
+      electricity/
+        electricity.csv
+      weather/
+        weather.csv
+```
+
+The checkpoint directory defaults to `../ckpt/` relative to `long_term_tsf`.
+
+## Quick Smoke Test
+
+From the repository root:
+
+```bash
+cd long_term_tsf
+CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0 bash scripts/vision_verification/run_ettm1_quick.sh
+```
+
+This runs `ETTm1` with `pred_len=96` only.
+
+## Official Zero-Shot Verification Suite
+
+From the repository root:
+
+```bash
+cd long_term_tsf
+CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0 bash scripts/vision_verification/run_official_ltsf_suite.sh
+```
+
+By default this runs:
+
+```text
+ETTm1 ETTm2 ETTh1 ETTh2 ECL Weather
+```
+
+with prediction lengths:
+
+```text
+96 192 336 720
+```
+
+Useful overrides:
+
+```bash
+DATASETS="ETTm1 Weather" PRED_LENS="96 192" CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0 \
+  bash scripts/vision_verification/run_official_ltsf_suite.sh
+
+ABLATIONS="none stats_only time_permute col_shuffle" PRED_LENS="96" \
+  bash scripts/vision_verification/run_ettm1_quick.sh
+
+RUN_SEASONAL_NAIVE=0 bash scripts/vision_verification/run_ettm1_quick.sh
+RUN_VISIONTS=0 bash scripts/vision_verification/run_ettm1_quick.sh
+```
+
+## Results
+
+Each run writes into:
+
+```text
+long_term_tsf/save/vision_verification/<DATA>/pl_<PRED_LEN>/<MODEL>/<VARIANT>/
+```
+
+The suite writes a summary CSV:
+
+```text
+long_term_tsf/save/vision_verification/summary.csv
+```
+
+You can regenerate it manually:
+
+```bash
+python scripts/vision_verification/summarize_verification.py \
+  --root save/vision_verification \
+  --out save/vision_verification/summary.csv
+```
+
+## Reading the Evidence
+
+- If `SeasonalNaive` is close to `VisionTS/none`, the periodic numerical prior is carrying much of the performance.
+- If `stats_only` is strong, mean/std normalization and level continuation are a serious baseline.
+- If `time_permute` remains strong, temporal ordering is less important than the value distribution.
+- If `row_shuffle`, `col_shuffle`, or `image_patch_shuffle` collapse, the rendered 2D geometry and MAE spatial prior matter.
